# General Rules

These rules apply to every file in the project.

## Terminology

Project conventions take precedence over any conflicting global rules:

- Presentation layer uses **Notifier** (`<feature>_notifier.dart` in `presentation/notifiers/`), not ViewModel.
- Abstractions use Dart 3 `abstract interface class`, not an `I*` prefix (e.g. `GameRepository`, not `IGameRepository`).
- Providers are declared via `@riverpod` codegen — one provider per file, no central `providers.dart` barrel.
- Use Case / Repository providers live in `features/<feature>/di/`; Notifier providers live in `presentation/notifiers/`. Never in `domain/`.

## Naming

- Use `PascalCase` for classes, enums, mixins and extensions.
- Use `camelCase` for variables, methods and parameters.
- Use `snake_case` for file and folder names.
- Prefix private members with `_`.

## File Organization

- Export only one public class, widget or extension per file.
- File name must match the exported type.
- Do not use barrel files (`index.dart`).

## Imports

Import order:

1. `dart:`
2. `package:flutter`
3. Third-party packages
4. Project imports

`package:` imports are mandatory for imports to `core/` and between layers within the same feature (e.g. `data` → `domain`).
Relative imports are tolerated only within the same layer/folder.
Direct imports between two features are strictly forbidden (see Feature Isolation).

## Clean Code

- One class = one responsibility.
- One method = one responsibility.
- Prefer explicit names over comments.
- Avoid duplicated code.
- Keep methods focused and easy to read.

## Null Safety

- Never use the null assertion operator (`!`).
- Extract nullable values into local variables before null checks.
- Avoid `late`.
- `late` is only allowed in test files.

## Typing

- Never use `dynamic`.
- Always use explicit types when they improve readability.

## Formatting

- Maximum line length: 120 characters.
- Always use trailing commas where supported.
- Remove unused imports.
- Remove dead code before committing.

## Logging

- Never use `print()`.
- Use Talker for application logging.

## Security

Never read, modify or expose secrets stored in configuration files.

## Codegen

- `freezed`: entities and states with multiple fields (e.g. `GameState`, `Board`).
- `json_serializable`: DTOs/models in the `data` layer requiring JSON serialization.
- Manual sealed classes allowed for simple, stable cases (e.g. `Result<T>`, `AppError`).
- Generated files (`.g.dart`, `.freezed.dart`) always committed.
- Never manually write code that `build_runner` can generate.
